17}}\n| birth_place      = [[Coburg]], Bavaria\n| death_date       = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| death_place      = \n| resting_place    = \n| occupation       = \n| language         = {{hlist\n  | German {{small|(primary)}}\n  | English\n}}\n| residence        = \n| nationality      = \n| citizenship      = \n| education        = \n| alma_mater       = [[University of Marburg]]\n| home_town        = \n| period           = \n| genre            = <!-- or: | genres = -->\n| subject          = <!-- or: | subjects = -->\n| movement         = \n| notableworks     = <!-- or: | notablework = -->\n| spouse           = <!-- or: | spouses = -->\n| partner          = <!-- or: | partners = -->\n| children         = \n| relatives        = \n| awards           = \n| signature        = \n| signature_alt    = \n| years_active     = \n| module           = \n| website          = <!-- {{URL|https://www.uni-marburg.de/de/fb06/neueste-geschichte/institut/zeitgeschichte/home}} -->\n| portaldisp       = <!-- \"on\", \"yes\", \"true\", etc.; or omit -->\n}}\n\n'''Dr. Eckart Conze''' (born October 17, 1963) is a German historian, author, and professor of [[modern history]] at the [[University of Marburg]] in Hesse.<ref name=\"university-of-marburg\" /><ref name=\"der-spiegel\" /> \n\nHe has authoried and co-authored more than thirty books and papers on modern German, European and international history,<ref name=\"german-national-library\" /> including works in English published by [[Cambridge University Press]].<ref name=\"cambridge-university-press\" /> His interviews and writing have appeared in German news magazine [[Der Spiegel]].<ref name=\"der-spiegel\" /><ref name=\"der-spiegel-wartime-ministry\" />\n\nHis book ''The Search for Security ({{lang-de|link=no|Die Suche nach Sicherheit}})''<ref name=\"search-for-security\" /> garnered him the prize for promoting the translation of humanities works by the [[B\u00f6rsenverein des Deutschen Buchhandels]] in 2009.<ref name=\"press-release-humanities-prize\" />\n\nHe was a member of the Independent Commission of Historians, tasked by the German [[Federal Foreign Office]] in 2005 to study the conduct of German diplomats in [[Nazi Germany]] and in the [[West Germany|Federal Republic]].<ref name=\"der-spiegel\" /><ref name=\"federal-foreign-office\" /> The commission published its findings on October 21, 2010 in a book entitled ''The Office and the Past ({{lang-de|link=no|Das Amt und die Vergangenheit}})''.<ref name=\"office-past\" />\n\nHe is the Deputy Chairperson of the Board of Trustees of the [[:de:Wolf-Erich-Kellner-Ged\u00e4chtnisstiftung|Wolf-Erich-Kellner Memorial Foundation]], commemorating its namesake German historian, archivist, and [[Free Democratic Party (Germany)|FDP]] politician.<ref name=\"foundation\" />\n\n==Literature==\n\n* {{cite book\n| trans-title = The Gaullistic Challenge: German-Franco Relations in American-European Policy\n| title       = Die gaullistische Herausforderung. Die deutsch-franz\u00f6sischen Beziehungen in der amerikanischen Europapolitik\n| language    = de\n| publisher   = [[University of Erlangen\u2013Nuremberg]]\n| date        = 1995\n| location    = [[Munich]]\n| isbn        = 3-486-56106-5\n}}\n* {{cite book\n| trans-title = From German Nobility: The Counts of Bernstorff in the Twentieth Century\n| title       = Von deutschem Adel. Die Grafen von Bernstorff im zwanzigsten Jahrhundert\n| language    = de\n| publisher   = [[Random House#International branches|Deutsche Verlags-Anstalt]]\n| date        = 2000\n| location    = [[Stuttgart]]\n| isbn        = 3-421-05344-8\n}}\n* {{cite book\n| trans-title = The Search for Security: A History of the Federal Republic From 1949 to the Present\n| title       = Die Suche nach Sicherheit. Eine Geschichte der Bundesrepublik von 1949 bis in die Gegenwart\n| language    = de\n| publisher   = Siedler\n| date        = 2009\n| location    = [[Munich]]\n| isbn        = 978-3-88680-919-6\n}}\n* {{cite 