ame=source2/><ref>{{cite web|title=Accessibility at USA Network|url=http://www.usanetwork.com/accessibility/|work=USANetwork.com|accessdate=July 3, 2012}}</ref>\n*''[[Colony (TV series)|Colony]]''\n*''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation]]'' (reruns)\n*''[[Donny!]]''\n*''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]'' (reruns)\n*''[[Modern Family]]'' (reruns)\n*''[[Motive (TV series)|Motive]]''\n*''[[Mr. Robot]]''\n*''[[NCIS (TV series)|NCIS]]'' (reruns)\n*''[[NCIS: Los Angeles]]'' (reruns)\n*''[[Playing House (TV series)|Playing House]]''\n*''[[Royal Pains]]''\n*''[[Suits (U.S. TV series)|Suits]]''\n*Some movies\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Retinitis Pigmentosa International#TheatreVision|TheatreVision]]\n* [[Radio drama]]\n* [[Novelization]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n# Cronin, Barry J. Ph.D. and Robertson King, Sharon, MA. \"[http://www2.edc.org/NCIP/library/v&c/cronin.htm The Development of the Descriptive Video Service]\", Report for the National Center to Improve Practice. Retrieved on July 30, 2007.\n# \"[http://main.wgbh.org/wgbh/pages/mag/resources/the-abcs-of-dvs.html The ABC's of DVS]\", WGBH - Media Access Group.  Retrieved on July 30, 2007.\n# \"[http://www.audiovisioncanada.com/ACCFMX/about.cfm Our Inclusive Approach]\", AudioVision. Retrieved on July 30, 2007.\n# [http://main.wgbh.org/wgbh/pages/mag/services/description/dvs-faq.html DVS FAQ], WGBH - Media Access Group. Retrieved on July 30, 2007.\n# \"[http://main.wgbh.org/wgbh/pages/mag/resources/guides/mag_guide_vol3.html Media Access Guide Volume 3]\", WGBH - Media Access Group. Retrieved on July 30, 2007.\n# \"[http://adinternational.org/ADIACB1.html ACB Statement on Video Description]\" American Council for the Blind Legislative Seminar 2006, February 1, 2006. Retrieved from Audio Description International on July 30, 2007.\n# [http://main.wgbh.org/wgbh/pages/mag/services/description/ontv/pbs-schedule.htm List of PBS series with DVS, August 2007]{{Dead link|date=July 2019 |bot=InternetArch